{
  "stem": "12494.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That is, immediately preceding March 19.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was-- he was a very unusual person, and I-- I feel privileged that I was able to observe him during these years.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He was a very ambitious person.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Ambitious for position, for influence, for hobnobbing with the Hungarian aristocracy whose-- whose forests he bought for his lumber mills.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He was a learned man, in a Jewish sense.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He had a yeshiva background.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he-- he was modern Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "By that I mean that he was quite Orthodox, but he, you know, didn't wear a beard, and he was a man of the world.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And starting about 1941, there was this tremendous change in this man, where he gradually abandoned all his business involvements, leaving it essentially up to his brother, and where he concentrated his life completely on the rescue mission.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- which then really culminated in-- in the occupation, when he refused to join the Jewish council.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was told by General Muzovski-- he was sort of an-- an-- an interesting influence.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The general convinced him that if he joins the Jewish Council-- not as employee, like I did, as a little guy, but as a-- in a capacity as a member of the council, a policy-making member of the council, that he would become a traitor to his people.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That-- that it was unavoidable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That all Polish Jewish council members finally had to wind up in that capacity.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he refused to cooperate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He-- he became very much convinced of that and withdrew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He accepted the protection papers, but he did not do anything but charitable activities.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
